30/03/2009
MADRID, Spain -- Police have made another arrest related to the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK), media reported on Sunday (March 29th). Authorities detained Eyyup Doru, a suspected PKK militant, in Madrid. His arrest followed that last week of Remzi Kartal, a former lawmaker from Turkey's disbanded Democracy Party, on an international arrest warrant for alleged crimes in Turkey. Kartal, a suspected former PKK commander, allegedly belonged to a terrorist organisation and committed illegal activities. He is in custody in Spain awaiting extradition.
In other news Sunday, Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan has ordered an investigation of last week's deadly helicopter crash in southern Turkey. Six people, including opposition Great Union Party leader Muhsin Yazicioglu, died in Wednesday's accident in the province of Kahramanmaras. Preliminary investigations indicate weather conditions caused the crash. (Anadolu news agency, NTV, CNN Turk, HaberTurk - 29/03/09)
